1
00:00:00,533 --> 00:00:01,633
(Episode 1: One Day, a Baby Appeared)

2
00:00:01,633 --> 00:00:02,800
Baby, what's up

3
00:00:03,467 --> 00:00:05,000
(The five TXT members get ready
for the baby's arrival.)

4
00:00:05,433 --> 00:00:06,433
Baby

5
00:00:06,633 --> 00:00:08,767
Still...

6
00:00:09,067 --> 00:00:10,700
this house has so many rounded edges,

7
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:11,767
even the couch.

8
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:12,867
This looks tasty.

9
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:14,500
Is this for me?

10
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,633
(Baby snacks)

11
00:00:15,633 --> 00:00:17,489
Are you seriously eating baby food
just because we're out of snacks?

12
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:18,900
Doesn't it look good, though?

13
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:21,100
It says it's for cleaning toys.

14
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:24,267
Toy sanitizer.

15
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:25,567
Is this a bowl?

16
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,700
- I think so.
- Later, when we're babysitting,

17
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,600
"Here comes the airplane!"

18
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:31,233
We can do this.

19
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:32,867
(Five rookie sitters can't wait.)

20
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:37,067
(Is the baby here?)

21
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:38,567
- He's here.
- Who's that?

22
00:00:38,567 --> 00:00:40,133
- Here he is.
- Is he?

23
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:41,167
- Has he arrived?
- Is he here?

24
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:42,167
I think he's really here.

25
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,267
- Should I open it?
- Yeah.

26
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,667
(The TOMORROW X TOGETHER uncles
are pumped.)

27
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:50,900
We got a delivery.

28
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:52,033
(What's in the bag?)

29
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,400
- Oh, look at this!
- Is it a book?

30
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,767
(A parenting diary from the baby's mom)

31
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:55,767
Let's see.

32
00:00:56,133 --> 00:00:58,033
"Hello, Yu Jun is..."

33
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:59,400
"a 14-month-old boy."

34
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:01,400
"He's very curious and full of energy."

35
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:04,100
He wakes up at 7:00 a.m.,

36
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:05,400
has lunch at noon,

37
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:08,300
and naps from 1:00 p.m. to 3:30 p.m.

38
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,700
(Sweet, nap time.)

39
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:11,700
His favorite is...

40
00:01:12,367 --> 00:01:13,367
a rice cracker?

41
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:14,900
An ink bottle?

42
00:01:15,133 --> 00:01:17,433
- I think it says rice crackers.
- There it is! Sliced rice crackers.

43
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,667
"Dear TOMORROW X TOGETHER,"

44
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:22,733
"If you approach Yu Jun slowly,"

45
00:01:22,733 --> 00:01:23,967
"he'll warm up to you faster."

46
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,600
"He loves active play."

47
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:29,100
"If he cries,
distract him with snacks or toys,"

48
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,233
"and he'll calm down in no time."

49
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:31,800
"He has the most fun outdoors."

50
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:32,833
"Please take good care of him."

51
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:34,633
Got it. When we're outside,

52
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,433
we need to wear him out.

53
00:01:36,433 --> 00:01:38,133
I'm going to give it my all
playing with him.

54
00:01:38,133 --> 00:01:39,333
(Will things go as planned?)

55
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:40,633
Let's do our best.

56
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,033
He goes to bed and wakes up pretty early.

57
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:46,167
- For sure.
- Babies are such early birds.

58
00:01:46,167 --> 00:01:47,167
They're living the dream.

59
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:49,533
I bet he's going to be so cute!

60
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:50,533
I know, right?

61
00:01:50,533 --> 00:01:52,533
This teddy bear has really long legs.

62
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:54,567
Let's pretend it's the baby...

63
00:01:54,567 --> 00:01:55,667
and take turns holding it.

64
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:57,600
- Does anyone know how?
- Is this too much?

65
00:01:58,167 --> 00:02:00,067
- You can't hold him like that.
- That would...

66
00:02:00,067 --> 00:02:01,167
even make Tori uncomfortable.

67
00:02:01,167 --> 00:02:02,467
Don't you hold them like this?

68
00:02:02,467 --> 00:02:03,633
Our legs should be positioned like this.

69
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:04,833
(YEONJUN shows off a weird pose.)

70
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:05,933
- This is...
- I don't think that's right.

71
00:02:05,933 --> 00:02:07,800
- You try.
- Isn't it like this?

72
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:09,233
Well...

73
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:11,833
- Yeah.
- Just like that.

74
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:13,267
Perfect. SOOBIN's got the hang of it.

75
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:15,467
This is the big one for today.

76
00:02:15,467 --> 00:02:17,167
I've never changed a diaper before.

77
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:18,833
- I bet none of us have.
- The dreaded diapers!

78
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:20,533
- Have you changed one?
- I have.

79
00:02:20,533 --> 00:02:22,067
- Just once.
- Seriously?

80
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:24,367
HUENINGKAI, try it on the doll.

81
00:02:24,367 --> 00:02:25,467
- Should I give it a shot?
- Yeah.

82
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:26,880
You're putting it on now?

83
00:02:27,533 --> 00:02:29,067
- I don't even know how to open it.
- You can't even get it open.

84
00:02:29,067 --> 00:02:30,467
Let's do this. SOOBIN, lie down.

85
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,300
Me?

86
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:34,200
It might only cover one butt cheek.

87
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,200
Take off your pants and lie down.
No way.

88
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,567
(Forcing it open)

89
00:02:38,567 --> 00:02:39,567
It smells good.

90
00:02:39,667 --> 00:02:41,033
- Really?
- Let me smell.

91
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:43,333
(Rookie sitters full of curiosity)

92
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:44,733
I bet it won't smell so good later.

93
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,500
- Did you poop?
- You pooped!

94
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,900
YEONJUN pooped!

95
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,767
Take your pants off.

96
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:52,739
Are there instructions?

97
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:54,767
Just stretch it and pull it on.

98
00:02:54,767 --> 00:02:57,200
These are pull-ups, not the tape kind.

99
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,233
We just slide them on.

100
00:02:58,367 --> 00:03:01,067
(Stuffing it in first)

101
00:03:01,133 --> 00:03:02,967
One leg at a time. Are we done?

102
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,533
It's a pull-up diaper.

103
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:07,600
I mean, a pull-up...

104
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:09,800
- A pull-up?
- We got it.

105
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,433
- We roll it up and toss it like this.
- Right.

106
00:03:11,433 --> 00:03:12,933
"Flush poop down the toilet,"

107
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:15,067
"wrap the diaper in tissue,
and put it in the bin."

108
00:03:15,567 --> 00:03:16,567
I'm nervous.

109
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:18,800
(Rookie sitters afraid
of making a mistake)

110
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:21,200
But I think we'll do great.

111
00:03:23,533 --> 00:03:26,300
(Is the baby actually here this time?)

112
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:28,000
- I think he's really here.
- The baby's here!

113
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,167
Why am I so nervous?

114
00:03:29,867 --> 00:03:32,867
(Heading to the door in white socks)

115
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:33,867
Hello?

116
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:36,067
(The door finally opens
for their first meeting.)

117
00:03:36,067 --> 00:03:37,167
Hi!

118
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:38,433
- Hello.
- Hi there!

119
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:41,500
(Hi!)

120
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:43,900
(Something just zoomed past.)

121
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:44,900
(Eyes locked)

122
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,400
- He's adorable.
- I know, right?

123
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:48,900
- He's so cute.
- Hi!

124
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:50,200
Hello, ma'am.

125
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,200
- Hello!
- Hi, hello.

126
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,800
(11:00 a.m., TXT meets Yu Jun
for the first time.)

127
00:03:55,067 --> 00:03:57,033
- He's so tiny.
- So cute!

128
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,767
He's smaller than the teddy bear!

129
00:03:58,767 --> 00:03:59,767
He really is so precious!

130
00:03:59,767 --> 00:04:01,100
I thought he'd be as big as the bear.

131
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:02,300
(Totally smitten)

132
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:03,300
So cute!

133
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:05,967
Watch your step.

134
00:04:06,933 --> 00:04:09,533
He's heading straight for it.

135
00:04:09,533 --> 00:04:10,867
- He's a good walker.
- Watch your step, little guy.

136
00:04:10,867 --> 00:04:13,167
(Choi Yu Jun, 14 months old)

137
00:04:13,167 --> 00:04:15,867
(Yu Jun, the high-energy baby...)

138
00:04:15,867 --> 00:04:19,233
(and five uncles
who are brand new to parenting,)

139
00:04:19,233 --> 00:04:20,600
(take on...)

140
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:23,400
(a wild mission...)

141
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:26,933
(to complete a chaotic parenting diary.)

142
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,500
(A peaceful start so far)

143
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:29,767
Yu Jun walks really well.

144
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:30,833
He's a pro.

145
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,967
- We've got a lot to do.
- Let's check his pants first.

146
00:04:33,267 --> 00:04:35,067
You could be an idol.

147
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:36,877
He knows exactly where the camera is.

148
00:04:36,967 --> 00:04:38,033
(Like meerkats)

149
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:39,133
Oops!

150
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,600
That scared me!

151
00:04:40,967 --> 00:04:42,000
(Rookie uncles worried
Yu Jun might get hurt)

152
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,033
Yu Jun!

153
00:04:43,267 --> 00:04:44,533
(Yu Jun is just having a blast.)

154
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:46,367
He walks so boldly, it's scary.

155
00:04:47,033 --> 00:04:48,033
Let's all walk.

156
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,567
- Let's walk together.
- Come here.

157
00:04:50,567 --> 00:04:51,567
I'm nervous.

158
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:52,633
Walk slowly.

159
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:56,233
(Following Yu Jun around)

160
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:58,567
- Let's just put them in the middle.
- Sure.

161
00:04:58,867 --> 00:05:00,500
- Wait, but...
- Wow, Yu Jun!

162
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,500
(Setting out mats for Yu Jun's safety)

163
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:04,133
(Tumbling down)

164
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:06,800
(Rookie sitters are on edge.)

165
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:09,000
(Taking off like a rocket)

166
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,400
(Yu Jun charges ahead.)

167
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,133
I get so anxious
when he's on the marble floor!

168
00:05:12,133 --> 00:05:13,967
I'll just stay right here.

169
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:15,300
You're strong, Yu Jun.

170
00:05:17,767 --> 00:05:19,233
You've got some power.

171
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:20,933
(Stepping back with all his might)

172
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:22,467
(Toddling along)

173
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:24,233
(A hallway race)

174
00:05:24,233 --> 00:05:25,833
You're walking so well. Good job!

175
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,067
Let's go again!

176
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:29,867
(Yu Jun goes straight for it.)

177
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:31,533
(Come here.)

178
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:33,333
(Pausing)

179
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,067
(Dying of cuteness)

180
00:05:35,067 --> 00:05:36,800
(The five uncles are obsessed
with Yu Jun.)

181
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:37,800
Yu Jun.

182
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,133
Are you afraid of me?

183
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:41,467
(Run for it.)

184
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:44,467
He's scared of you.

185
00:05:44,467 --> 00:05:46,467
I should wait for him to come to me.

186
00:05:47,367 --> 00:05:50,100
He seems to really like this step.

187
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,933
Let's block off this whole area.

188
00:05:51,967 --> 00:05:54,033
(Yu Jun is all over the place.)

189
00:05:54,033 --> 00:05:55,033
(Yu Jun's parade)

190
00:05:55,033 --> 00:05:56,067
Wow, Yu Jun.

191
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:57,400
You're a great walker.

192
00:05:58,267 --> 00:05:59,367
He's so good at walking.

193
00:05:59,367 --> 00:06:01,433
He's getting a serious leg workout today.

194
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,867
(Deep squats this time)

195
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,567
(Running again)

196
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:12,533
(Running mates)

197
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:15,400
(This uncle is weird.)

198
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,400
He's so cute!

199
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:20,167
(A moment of appreciation)

200
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:26,033
(TXT's reactions are getting
better already.)

201
00:06:29,067 --> 00:06:30,400
(Clapping like a seal)

202
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:32,433
(Happy)

203
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:34,833
(Yu Jun's favorite move: clapping)

204
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:36,900
- He's clapping too!
- Oh, my gosh!

205
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:40,133
(Parenting fact:
If they like it, it's on repeat.)

206
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,967
You want me to open it?

207
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:47,100
(You're the best.)

208
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:49,200
- He's actually a great communicator.
- He communicates so well.

209
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,200
(Sneezing)

210
00:06:50,567 --> 00:06:51,567
(Don't catch a cold, Yu Jun.)

211
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:53,346
I should wipe his nose when he comes back.

212
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:56,133
I need to wipe his nose.

213
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,967
Here's a wet wipe.

214
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,633
(Wiping his nose with a bib)

215
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,600
All clean.

216
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,333
(Reward: a squishy cheek)

217
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:04,667
- What a cutie.
- Oh, man!

218
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:07,533
(I see. So that's the story.)

219
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:08,833
Are you done?
Should we go to the next page?

220
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:12,800
(Forget that, just clap.)

221
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:16,467
(TXT and Yu Jun are bonding.)

222
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,000
It's almost lunchtime.

223
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:21,500
Yu Jun, want to take a break?

224
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,000
(Laughing)

225
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,033
We should start preparing his food.

226
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:26,600
It's lunch time.

227
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,633
Then make us some legendary pasta.

228
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:30,067
Got it. Tomato pasta coming up.

229
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:31,933
(TAEHYUN is today's chef)

230
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:32,967
I believe in you.

231
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:35,333
I've got four "big babies" to feed too.

232
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:36,333
Yu Jun!

233
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:37,533
(Big Baby 3 and Big Baby 5 appear.)

234
00:07:37,533 --> 00:07:38,533
BEOMGYU!

235
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:41,867
(Bravo!)

236
00:07:41,867 --> 00:07:42,900
(Pausing)

237
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:43,933
Want an airplane ride?

238
00:07:43,933 --> 00:07:44,933
(Two uncle-planes ready for takeoff)

239
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:46,067
This is so much fun.

240
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:47,467
That's it. Come here.

241
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,100
I'm wiped out.

242
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:51,967
(YEONJUN's plane takes off.)

243
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:54,567
(YEONJUN's plane grounded immediately)

244
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,600
(Staring)

245
00:07:59,867 --> 00:08:01,067
- Mom.
- Mom?

246
00:08:01,067 --> 00:08:02,200
(I'm out of here.)

247
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:05,367
(Disembarking after a flight delay)

248
00:08:06,133 --> 00:08:07,167
Are you okay?

249
00:08:07,633 --> 00:08:08,855
You're the one who started it.

250
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:12,000
He looks so huggable.

251
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,900
(Melting from the view)

252
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:14,933
Yu Jun.

253
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:18,267
I'll give you a ride, Yu Jun.

254
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:19,733
(Already moved on to another pilot)

255
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:21,067
Oh, my gosh!

256
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:22,633
Let's go!

257
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:23,767
(Roaring)

258
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:27,267
(Giggling)

259
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:29,900
(A high-pitched dolphin laugh)

260
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,067
He's giggling!

261
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:32,167
(SOOBIN, the spectator)

262
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,333
(Giggling)

263
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:34,833
(YEONJUN is hooked on that laugh.)

264
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:35,867
Me too!

265
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:37,900
I want a turn!

266
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:39,500
I can hear him giggling.

267
00:08:39,733 --> 00:08:40,767
Yu Jun, you ready?

268
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:42,067
(Refusing the ride)

269
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:43,300
No? Are you ready?

270
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:44,867
No?

271
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:47,267
(Look at me, please.)

272
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,800
Shall we go?

273
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:50,167
(Yes.)

274
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:51,933
There we go!

275
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:54,200
(BEOMGYU's jet lifts off.)

276
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,567
(BEOMGYU uses three days' worth
of energy for Yu Jun.)

277
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:57,567
(Squealing)

278
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:01,233
(Field report on BEOMGYU's parenting)

279
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:02,900
(Jealous)

280
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:04,067
(Giggling)

281
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:05,933
Let's fly!

282
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:09,300
I can do this.

283
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:11,800
Hurry up.

284
00:09:12,233 --> 00:09:13,600
(Yu Jun's endorphins are at 100 percent.)

285
00:09:13,733 --> 00:09:14,833
My turn with Yu Jun.

286
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,333
(YEONJUN licks his lips.)

287
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:18,167
- So hot.
- Yu Jun, let's go.

288
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,467
(Roaring)

289
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,300
(A weak engine despite the spirit)

290
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,867
(Uncomfortable)

291
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:26,567
(The flight ends in disappointment.)

292
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:27,867
(Pity)

293
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:30,467
Is there a way to make the baby food?

294
00:09:30,467 --> 00:09:32,033
- This is it.
- This?

295
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,500
- This one?
- Yeah.

296
00:09:33,525 --> 00:09:35,125
- You just have to heat it up.
- Really?

297
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:39,600
(Yu Jun plays with the other uncles.)

298
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:42,900
(What's this?)

299
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:45,133
(Yu Jun is fascinated by the camera.)

300
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:46,300
(Oops)

301
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:50,267
(Cool enough to shrug off a trip)

302
00:09:51,638 --> 00:09:52,633
Heave-ho!

303
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:53,800
(Heave-ho)

304
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,467
(Mister!)

305
00:09:55,467 --> 00:09:57,767
(Have some water!)

306
00:09:58,567 --> 00:10:01,500
(Even kind enough to share his water)

307
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,000
So hot!

308
00:10:03,025 --> 00:10:04,166
(Putting the warmed baby food into a bowl)

309
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:05,633
It's a perfect, proper meal.

310
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:08,966
(Meanwhile, TAEHYUN is making
scrambled eggs.)

311
00:10:08,966 --> 00:10:11,200
(Concentrating hard)

312
00:10:11,866 --> 00:10:13,166
Oh, nice.

313
00:10:13,166 --> 00:10:15,100
(Mixed with the baby food,
Yu Jun's favorite meal is ready.)

314
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:15,933
Done.

315
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:17,866
Shall we eat, Yu Jun?

316
00:10:18,766 --> 00:10:19,800
Yu Jun.

317
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,633
Hungry? Let's eat.

318
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,200
You want some?

319
00:10:23,866 --> 00:10:26,500
- Yu Jun, it's time to eat, okay?
- Let's eat.

320
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,300
Time for lunch.

321
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,266
Come here, Yu Jun.

322
00:10:29,933 --> 00:10:30,533
(Stepping up)

323
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,933
Sit right here.

324
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:33,733
Good boy.

325
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,133
Let's eat.

326
00:10:35,966 --> 00:10:38,733
(YEONJUN is feeding a baby
for the first time.)

327
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:39,633
Oh, no.

328
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,066
(Opening wide)

329
00:10:41,066 --> 00:10:42,066
Goodness!

330
00:10:42,066 --> 00:10:43,133
(Spitting it out)

331
00:10:43,133 --> 00:10:44,366
Is it too hot?

332
00:10:44,366 --> 00:10:45,466
(He spat it out because it was too hot.)

333
00:10:45,466 --> 00:10:46,433
- It's too hot.
- I'm sorry!

334
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:47,800
Was it too hot? My bad.

335
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,866
Let me cool it down a bit.

336
00:10:48,866 --> 00:10:50,466
Okay.

337
00:10:50,466 --> 00:10:51,633
Blow on it.

338
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:53,833
- Isn't that a bit much?
- You think so?

339
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:54,933
Here you go.

340
00:10:54,933 --> 00:10:55,700
(Second attempt)

341
00:10:56,766 --> 00:10:59,033
- It's still too hot.
- It must be hot.

342
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,159
I thought I had cooled it down enough.

343
00:11:01,133 --> 00:11:02,300
(Blowing on it)

344
00:11:02,566 --> 00:11:04,233
- Yu Jun.
- I mashed it up.

345
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:06,633
Yu Jun, let's eat.

346
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,433
(The food didn't cool down,
but his interest did.)

347
00:11:09,666 --> 00:11:11,433
How am I supposed to cool this thing down?

348
00:11:11,433 --> 00:11:13,900
Just let it sit for about ten minutes.

349
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,766
Okay. Yu Jun, I'll cool it down some more.

350
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:18,333
(Using a hand-powered fan)

351
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:23,833
(A Billboard 200 artist is fanning
baby food with a picture book.)

352
00:11:26,166 --> 00:11:26,966
Yu Jun.

353
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,300
Want to eat now?

354
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,800
(He can't hear him)

355
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:31,858
Yu Jun.

356
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:33,633
Yu Jun.

357
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:35,200
Yu Jun?

358
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,433
If you don't eat this, we will.

359
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:39,866
- You're going to lose your lunch.
- We'll finish it all!

360
00:11:39,866 --> 00:11:41,033
I could eat this in one bite.

361
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:43,733
If YEONJUN and I each take a bite,
it's gone.

362
00:11:43,733 --> 00:11:45,833
(Watch out, they might actually do it.)

363
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,033
Yu Jun.

364
00:11:48,433 --> 00:11:49,233
Want some food?

365
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:51,333
Are you hungry?

366
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:52,400
(Finally, Yu Jun looks his way.)

367
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,400
(Seizing the moment)

368
00:11:56,033 --> 00:12:00,000
(The uncles gather, sensing an opening.)

369
00:12:01,366 --> 00:12:02,133
(Blowing on the food)

370
00:12:02,766 --> 00:12:03,766
Yu Jun.

371
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,200
Yu Jun, here comes the food.

372
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,233
(Opening wide)

373
00:12:07,766 --> 00:12:08,633
What a sweetheart!

374
00:12:08,633 --> 00:12:11,733
(Getting him to take his first bite
on the third try)

375
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:12,566
Want some more?

376
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,133
(Yummy)

377
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:16,366
Yu Jun, let's have another bite.

378
00:12:16,366 --> 00:12:18,933
(The uncles keep the momentum going.)

379
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:20,900
Isn't that too much for one spoonful?

380
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:23,233
Not every baby eats as much as you do.

381
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:25,100
(A heavy eater)

382
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,200
Is this much okay, then?

383
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,966
- Just a little at a time.
- Got it.

384
00:12:27,966 --> 00:12:30,133
- My sister feeds her baby tiny bites.
- Really?

385
00:12:30,466 --> 00:12:31,766
(The ultimate airplane trick)

386
00:12:31,766 --> 00:12:33,266
Here comes the airplane!

387
00:12:33,266 --> 00:12:34,700
(Give it to me already!)

388
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:38,133
(Bouncing)

389
00:12:39,566 --> 00:12:41,500
He loves your airplane technique.

390
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:44,200
(Finally, Yu Jun is focused on his meal.)

391
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,000
(I want this one.)

392
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:46,800
You want this?

393
00:12:48,133 --> 00:12:49,633
(He even picks what he wants to eat.)

394
00:12:49,633 --> 00:12:51,066
He's eating so well.

395
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:55,066
YEONJUN is feeding you.

396
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:56,233
Good boy.

397
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:57,533
Is it tasty?

398
00:12:58,133 --> 00:12:59,166
Is it good?

399
00:12:59,166 --> 00:13:00,233
(Getting up)

400
00:13:00,233 --> 00:13:01,133
(Bye.)

401
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:02,442
Are you done already?

402
00:13:02,866 --> 00:13:03,633
Wait, what?
(Leaving after only five spoonfuls)

403
00:13:04,433 --> 00:13:05,833
(Following him)

404
00:13:06,366 --> 00:13:08,100
(It's not easy.)

405
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,866
(Yu Jun enters the kitchen.)

406
00:13:11,866 --> 00:13:15,033
(Happy)

407
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:19,433
(And now he's in the bedroom.)

408
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,033
Plop!

409
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:23,633
Oh, man.

410
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:27,033
(Catch me if you can.)

411
00:13:29,133 --> 00:13:32,633
Yu Jun, here you go!

412
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:33,566
(Following him around to feed him)

413
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:36,300
Yu Jun.

414
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:40,000
(HUENINGKAI's airplane is taking off.)

415
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,866
Your meal is here.

416
00:13:44,366 --> 00:13:47,466
- Good job!
- Good boy!

417
00:13:47,466 --> 00:13:49,166
(The VVIP is satisfied
with the airplane service.)

418
00:13:49,166 --> 00:13:50,233
Well done.

419
00:13:50,633 --> 00:13:52,800
(However, he's quickly distracted again.)

420
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:56,400
(Planning his escape
while looking out the window)

421
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,300
(Trying to make a break for it
down the hallway)

422
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,100
He really never stops moving.

423
00:14:00,566 --> 00:14:01,566
(Parenting diary tip)
(He's very curious and full of energy.)

424
00:14:02,566 --> 00:14:03,666
(He loves exploring
instead of sitting still.)

425
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:06,866
(The airplane is back to catch him.)

426
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,700
- Good job.
- Good boy.

427
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:12,366
(Clap for me!)

428
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:14,633
Gotcha.

429
00:14:14,633 --> 00:14:16,633
(They caught him in the bedroom,)

430
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:19,466
(but he bolted for the utility room.)

431
00:14:19,466 --> 00:14:20,666
Yu Jun, you want to see what I'm doing?

432
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:21,966
Yu Jun, let's go finish eating.

433
00:14:22,266 --> 00:14:23,533
(Caught ya!)

434
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:24,731
Shall we keep eating?

435
00:14:27,866 --> 00:14:29,066
(They got me)

436
00:14:29,066 --> 00:14:29,900
Open wide.

437
00:14:30,966 --> 00:14:32,066
Open wide, Yu Jun.

438
00:14:32,366 --> 00:14:33,200
Open up.

439
00:14:33,766 --> 00:14:36,800
(They finally get him back
for another bite.)

440
00:14:39,266 --> 00:14:40,100
(Getting emotional)

441
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,133
Mom, thanks for giving birth to me.

442
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:45,466
(Drinking)

443
00:14:45,666 --> 00:14:48,133
Mom, thank you for giving birth
to me and raising me.

444
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,900
He hasn't eaten much yet.

445
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:51,833
He needs to eat more.

446
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:52,666
Do you want some water?

447
00:14:52,666 --> 00:14:55,200
(Trying to find an opening
while he drinks)

448
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:58,033
You're such a good drinker.

449
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:00,300
Want some more?

450
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:02,233
One more time?

451
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:05,466
(Yu Jun must be thirsty
from all that running.)

452
00:15:05,466 --> 00:15:06,400
- He's really drinking a lot.
- Good boy.

453
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:08,833
Come here.

454
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:09,776
Let me wipe your nose.

455
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,500
Yu Jun, here comes the food.

456
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,100
(His eyes are full of love
while Yu Jun's nose runs nonstop.)

457
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,200
It's all over your face.

458
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:18,166
(Making airplane noises)

459
00:15:18,433 --> 00:15:20,966
- Good job.
- Well done.

460
00:15:21,866 --> 00:15:22,666
Here you go.

461
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:25,866
(YEONJUN wipes up the spilled food.)

462
00:15:25,866 --> 00:15:28,166
(Obsessed with cleanliness)

463
00:15:28,166 --> 00:15:32,000
(Parenting means
never standing up straight.)

464
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,366
This is exhausting.

465
00:15:37,633 --> 00:15:40,000
(But I'm not tired.)

466
00:15:40,766 --> 00:15:42,200
(Plopping down)

467
00:15:42,766 --> 00:15:45,833
I just gave the baby airplane rides,
and I'm totally drained.

468
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,966
(The version of us from 25 minutes ago
feels like a past life.)

469
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:51,766
(Kicking)

470
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:57,033
(Yu Jun walks past
after giving him a lesson.)

471
00:15:57,466 --> 00:15:58,933
(Wide awake)

472
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:00,966
(Meanwhile, TAEHYUN is
still cooking tirelessly.)

473
00:16:00,966 --> 00:16:04,400
(Spaghetti mode: activated)

474
00:16:06,066 --> 00:16:09,266
(Flawless two-handed skills)

475
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,666
(The meal for the "big babies"
is ready too.)

476
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:13,433
Don't you think...

477
00:16:14,066 --> 00:16:16,933
we should put Yu Jun down for a nap
before we eat?

478
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:18,933
You think so?
Then we have to finish this first.

479
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:21,700
But I don't think
he's ever going to sleep.

480
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:24,066
I don't think he gets food comas.

481
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:25,700
(A shower left running)

482
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:27,733
Let's play rock-paper-scissors
to split into groups of 2 and 3.

483
00:16:27,733 --> 00:16:29,833
Let's do that and eat separately.

484
00:16:30,166 --> 00:16:31,100
Good idea.
(Feeding him another spoonful)

485
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:33,633
Good boy.

486
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:34,666
(Proud)

487
00:16:34,666 --> 00:16:36,200
We can take turns eating...

488
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,666
- and watching the baby.
- Right.

489
00:16:37,666 --> 00:16:39,266
Just give up on sitting down.

490
00:16:39,266 --> 00:16:40,533
- For sure.
- Exactly.

491
00:16:40,533 --> 00:16:43,033
Babysitting means no sitting.

492
00:16:43,033 --> 00:16:44,700
I'll give you each a fork,
just come and eat.

493
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:45,566
(Toddling)

494
00:16:45,566 --> 00:16:47,733
- Eat one bite at a time.
- Let's just hurry up and eat.

495
00:16:47,733 --> 00:16:49,800
(Let's experience Yu Jun's nose touch.)

496
00:16:50,633 --> 00:16:52,000
Yu Jun, let me have a bite.

497
00:16:52,266 --> 00:16:53,900
Yu Jun, where are you going?

498
00:16:54,266 --> 00:16:55,933
Come play with me.

499
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:57,800
(Slurping)

500
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:00,700
Here you go.

501
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:02,100
It's here.

502
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,200
Good.

503
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,433
Look at him sweat.

504
00:17:05,066 --> 00:17:05,933
- I'm sweating too.
- You do?

505
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:09,533
(This is what they call
the parenting diet.)

506
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:11,075
SOOBIN, BEOMGYU, come and eat.

507
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,233
Go get some food.

508
00:17:12,233 --> 00:17:14,400
- Just take a bite and come back.
- Hurry up.

509
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:16,333
(Feeding duty switch)

510
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,100
Open wide, Yu Jun.

511
00:17:18,366 --> 00:17:19,833
He looks so cute on camera.

512
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,266
- He's adorable.
- You're so cute.

513
00:17:21,566 --> 00:17:24,500
(The airplane pilot finally takes
his first bite.)

514
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:26,700
(Choking)

515
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,633
(Eating in a rush)

516
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:32,800
Eat fast.

517
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:35,033
(Feeding Yu Jun a bite)

518
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:37,400
- Good boy.
- Well done.

519
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:40,600
(The rotating meal challenge)

520
00:17:41,266 --> 00:17:44,200
(No time to even sit down)

521
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,800
If he eats here and falls asleep,
that would be the dream.

522
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:50,766
(A hopeful spoonful of baby food)

523
00:17:50,766 --> 00:17:51,766
Good boy.

524
00:17:51,766 --> 00:17:53,433
Can someone grab his water bottle?

525
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,833
(It was a mealtime battle,)

526
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:58,666
(but they made it to the last bite.)

527
00:17:58,933 --> 00:18:01,133
(Lunch mission: accomplished!)

528
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:02,200
We did it!

529
00:18:02,433 --> 00:18:04,133
(Ten hours left until they're off duty.)

530
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:05,566
Ten hours?
Tell me you're joking.

531
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:10,733
(I'm smiling, but I'm not actually happy.)

532
00:18:10,733 --> 00:18:11,766
Don't lie to me.

533
00:18:12,166 --> 00:18:13,666
- It'll be better once he's asleep.
- No way.

534
00:18:13,666 --> 00:18:15,700
Ten more hours? That's ridiculous.

535
00:18:16,433 --> 00:18:18,900
- Let's go.
- Isn't there a sleep-inducing frequency?

536
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:19,766
Come with me.

537
00:18:20,866 --> 00:18:21,666
Where do you want to go?
(Well...)

538
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:23,766
(The uncles keep eating.)

539
00:18:23,766 --> 00:18:24,804
Does anyone need water?

540
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:26,966
Me.

541
00:18:26,966 --> 00:18:28,233
Do you have soda?

542
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:29,633
- Which kind?
- Is there anything else to drink?

543
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:30,466
(YEONJUN is thirsty.)

544
00:18:30,666 --> 00:18:32,111
Can you grab me that beer up there?

545
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:33,700
There's only beer here.

546
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:36,266
(He's never wanted a beer more
in his life.)

547
00:18:37,066 --> 00:18:38,033
(Passing him a cola instead)

548
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:39,218
Anyone want a Pepsi?

549
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,100
I'm just glad he ate enough.

550
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:45,600
We've cleared about two missions, right?

551
00:18:45,933 --> 00:18:47,300
Playing and feeding.

552
00:18:47,766 --> 00:18:48,600
Right.

553
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:51,800
(He can't stop laughing in disbelief.)

554
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,033
(Spotting Yu Jun)

555
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:54,066
(Happy)

556
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:55,566
(Now that he's full, he feels great.)

557
00:18:55,566 --> 00:18:56,800
(Yay!)

558
00:18:58,833 --> 00:19:02,166
(From 1:00 p.m. to 3:30 p.m.,
Yu Jun's nap time)

559
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:03,233
(Practicing with a teddy bear)

560
00:19:03,233 --> 00:19:04,100
Okay.

561
00:19:04,733 --> 00:19:06,166
(Whining)

562
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,333
Hang in there, everyone.

563
00:19:08,866 --> 00:19:10,000
- We will.
- We've got this.

564
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,684
- Are you done eating?
- We can definitely get him to sleep.

565
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:12,866
If you're finished, I'll clean up.

566
00:19:12,866 --> 00:19:13,900
He doesn't want to go in.

567
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,766
All right.

568
00:19:15,766 --> 00:19:17,333
(Difficulty level 4:
Putting Yu Jun to sleep)

569
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:18,700
All right.

570
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,633
(I don't want to go to sleep!)

571
00:19:22,866 --> 00:19:25,466
(It's not easy from the get-go.)

572
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:28,166
(Tiny, precious Yu Jun is being carried.)

573
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:31,633
Yu Jun, shall we go to sleep?

574
00:19:31,633 --> 00:19:33,066
(YEONJUN brought a pacifier.)

575
00:19:33,266 --> 00:19:34,633
Is it okay if he sleeps with this
in his mouth?

576
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:35,800
He can only sleep with it.

577
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:36,666
Is that right?

578
00:19:36,866 --> 00:19:37,800
He's so cute.

579
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,066
(He's totally smitten.)

580
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:41,733
(SOOBIN starts by rocking him to sleep.)

581
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:43,900
They said he sleeps better in the dark.

582
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:46,133
- Really?
- Yeah. Go into the bedroom...

583
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:47,000
and close the curtains.

584
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,466
(Hurrying to the bedroom)

585
00:19:49,466 --> 00:19:53,200
(Setting the mood for Yu Jun's nap)

586
00:19:54,166 --> 00:19:55,800
I think that's the switch.

587
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,600
- Mom.
- "Mom?"

588
00:19:58,320 --> 00:19:59,847
Mom.

589
00:20:00,366 --> 00:20:01,266
I'm the mommy.

590
00:20:03,135 --> 00:20:04,302
Let me be his mommy.

591
00:20:06,021 --> 00:20:07,773
I heard walking around helps.

592
00:20:07,774 --> 00:20:08,606
Right.

593
00:20:11,677 --> 00:20:12,944
He's calmer now.

594
00:20:12,945 --> 00:20:14,379
(Ten minutes later)

595
00:20:14,551 --> 00:20:16,214
(Is he pretending to sleep?)

596
00:20:18,117 --> 00:20:19,784
His eyes are wide open.

597
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,054
(Making eye contact with Uncle BEOMGYU)

598
00:20:26,159 --> 00:20:28,025
You don't want to take a nap at all,
do you?

599
00:20:28,928 --> 00:20:30,262
Why am I getting sleepy?

600
00:20:34,667 --> 00:20:35,634
I have an idea.

601
00:20:35,635 --> 00:20:36,968
(YEONJUN suddenly jumps up
to get something.)

602
00:20:36,969 --> 00:20:38,578
- What is everyone doing?
- We're trying to let him sleep.

603
00:20:39,038 --> 00:20:42,540
(He's out to the living room
to get a blanket for Yu Jun.)

604
00:20:43,509 --> 00:20:47,145
(He carefully spreads out the blanket
to make the room cozier.)

605
00:20:49,815 --> 00:20:50,782
(Snuggling)

606
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,684
SOOBIN, let me know
when your arms get tired.

607
00:20:52,885 --> 00:20:53,751
I'll hold him.

608
00:20:55,688 --> 00:20:56,588
(Turning his head around)

609
00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:57,922
(Not yet)

610
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:03,595
I think he needs to lean
on my shoulder to fall asleep.

611
00:21:03,596 --> 00:21:05,864
But he's basically standing.

612
00:21:06,832 --> 00:21:07,999
Yu Jun, lean on me and go to sleep.

613
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,133
(No!)

614
00:21:10,336 --> 00:21:11,369
(Yu Jun wants to keep playing!)

615
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:13,538
(I want to play with the camera.)

616
00:21:13,873 --> 00:21:15,907
(He's curious about this camera too.)

617
00:21:15,908 --> 00:21:16,975
Did the camera catch your attention?

618
00:21:16,976 --> 00:21:18,276
(Making eye contact)

619
00:21:18,978 --> 00:21:21,713
(He keeps looking for the cameras
instead of falling asleep.)

620
00:21:23,693 --> 00:21:27,218
(Serving up pure, innocent visuals
and racking up those fancam views.)

621
00:21:28,154 --> 00:21:30,722
(Meanwhile, what is TAEHYUN doing?)

622
00:21:31,691 --> 00:21:34,259
(Here comes the dishwashing robot!)

623
00:21:35,661 --> 00:21:39,664
(He's quietly doing ASMR.)

624
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:43,534
(His arms slowly start to drop.)

625
00:21:43,836 --> 00:21:44,702
Yu Jun.
Careful.

626
00:21:45,938 --> 00:21:47,672
- Do you want to hold him?
- Can I?

627
00:21:49,281 --> 00:21:50,748
- Be careful.
- You can hold him like this.

628
00:21:50,749 --> 00:21:52,216
(They're taking turns being Yu Jun's bed.)

629
00:21:53,166 --> 00:21:53,778
(No!)
All right.

630
00:21:54,493 --> 00:21:55,506
(Switch failed.)

631
00:21:55,514 --> 00:21:56,481
He wants you to hold him.

632
00:21:57,750 --> 00:21:58,583
(SOOBIN's arm workout continues.)

633
00:21:58,584 --> 00:21:59,651
Please fall asleep, then.

634
00:22:00,666 --> 00:22:01,838
I'm glad you like me, but...

635
00:22:02,788 --> 00:22:04,781
I think he feels just right in your arms.

636
00:22:08,060 --> 00:22:10,011
- Me?
- You want to go to YEONJUN?

637
00:22:11,864 --> 00:22:12,831
(Standing up)

638
00:22:12,832 --> 00:22:15,166
Give him to me.
Let me try putting him to sleep.

639
00:22:15,968 --> 00:22:17,468
(Another attempt
to switch Yu Jun's human role)

640
00:22:17,469 --> 00:22:18,303
Come here.

641
00:22:18,738 --> 00:22:20,938
- Don't you want to try YEONJUN?
- Come on.

642
00:22:21,574 --> 00:22:22,644
Let me help you sleep.

643
00:22:23,843 --> 00:22:26,245
(They manage to move him
out of SOOBIN's arms.)

644
00:22:26,246 --> 00:22:27,144
(Squirming)
You let him go first.

645
00:22:30,834 --> 00:22:32,150
It's okay. Get some sleep.

646
00:22:32,151 --> 00:22:34,081
(He unsteadily falls into YEONJUN's arms.)

647
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:38,123
(Wait. Did it work?)

648
00:22:39,558 --> 00:22:40,391
(I want to go back.)
No?

649
00:22:42,628 --> 00:22:43,931
(You said you wanted to be my mommy!)

650
00:22:43,932 --> 00:22:44,888
He feels coziest in your arms.

651
00:22:45,791 --> 00:22:47,892
- Okay.
- He's used to you.

652
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:48,700
(SOOBIN is the chosen one.)

653
00:22:49,168 --> 00:22:50,969
- I feel like I'm a cat tower.
- "I like this one!"

654
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:52,504
Since SOOBIN is tall,

655
00:22:52,505 --> 00:22:53,771
maybe he likes the height.

656
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:55,373
(Patting in disappointment)

657
00:22:57,610 --> 00:22:58,677
I'm done dishwashing.

658
00:22:58,678 --> 00:22:59,678
(It's been 30 minutes trying
to get him to nap.)

659
00:22:59,979 --> 00:23:00,845
Go to sleep.

660
00:23:02,281 --> 00:23:03,615
Should we pretend to sleep?

661
00:23:04,617 --> 00:23:06,184
(Will he finally fall asleep?)

662
00:23:06,185 --> 00:23:07,185
He's leaning.

663
00:23:07,186 --> 00:23:07,919
(Getting back up!)

664
00:23:08,856 --> 00:23:10,989
(You got fooled.)

665
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:16,193
(You keep making me smile.)

666
00:23:16,194 --> 00:23:17,128
Let's try again.

667
00:23:18,831 --> 00:23:19,931
SOOBIN, the veins in your arms...

668
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:22,299
They're popping.

669
00:23:22,668 --> 00:23:24,186
So I don't need to work out today, right?

670
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:25,904
(Kind Yu Jun keeps SOOBIN healthy.)

671
00:23:25,905 --> 00:23:26,905
Is it too hot in here for him?

672
00:23:28,207 --> 00:23:29,807
Let's bring something else.

673
00:23:30,109 --> 00:23:31,142
He feels a bit hot.

674
00:23:31,143 --> 00:23:33,311
- I think this is better.
- Let me try.

675
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:36,047
Yu Jun, are you ready?

676
00:23:36,749 --> 00:23:37,515
There you go.

677
00:23:37,516 --> 00:23:38,783
(YEONJUN tries again to be the human bed.)

678
00:23:38,784 --> 00:23:39,584
Let's try this.

679
00:23:39,753 --> 00:23:41,184
- Let's try this once.
- Let's do it.

680
00:23:41,453 --> 00:23:42,554
Uncle SOOBIN feels too hot, Yu Jun.

681
00:23:42,555 --> 00:23:44,855
- Come on, let's try just once.
- SOOBIN needs to cool down.

682
00:23:45,591 --> 00:23:46,892
I know. Just try it once.

683
00:23:46,893 --> 00:23:47,892
Let's try it this time.

684
00:23:47,893 --> 00:23:49,727
(I told you to leave me alone!)

685
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:51,195
(Grabbing)

686
00:23:51,196 --> 00:23:53,064
Hold on.

687
00:23:53,599 --> 00:23:54,532
He won't let you go.

688
00:23:54,533 --> 00:23:56,568
He's doing his best to stick with you.

689
00:23:56,569 --> 00:23:57,902
He's grabbing his collar.

690
00:23:58,103 --> 00:23:58,970
(Laughing)

691
00:23:58,971 --> 00:24:00,037
If that's the case...

692
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:01,973
Someone needs to hold him
for just a second.

693
00:24:01,974 --> 00:24:03,274
Just once second.

694
00:24:03,576 --> 00:24:05,443
Hold on a second.

695
00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:07,178
- Hold on.
- It's okay.

696
00:24:07,179 --> 00:24:08,346
We got it.

697
00:24:08,347 --> 00:24:09,481
(They're doing their best
to put him to sleep.)

698
00:24:09,482 --> 00:24:11,449
(Let go of me!)

699
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:12,484
He's not letting go.

700
00:24:12,485 --> 00:24:13,818
Yu Jun, just a second.

701
00:24:13,819 --> 00:24:14,953
(SOOBIN's getting happily slimmer.)

702
00:24:15,020 --> 00:24:16,787
I got it. I won't let go of you.

703
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:18,089
I'll keep holding you.

704
00:24:18,757 --> 00:24:20,191
What's wrong?

705
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:21,692
Let's empty this room for SOOBIN.

706
00:24:21,693 --> 00:24:22,793
Okay.

707
00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:25,029
Sorry. Please don't cry.

708
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:25,897
Night-night, Yu Jun.

709
00:24:25,898 --> 00:24:28,032
If you feel uncomfortable,
just wear this...

710
00:24:28,534 --> 00:24:30,068
What is it? Are you upset
seeing them leave?

711
00:24:30,603 --> 00:24:32,337
You don't want them to leave?

712
00:24:33,439 --> 00:24:35,340
- Should we go out?
- Should we call YEONJUN?

713
00:24:35,341 --> 00:24:36,508
I thought so too.

714
00:24:36,509 --> 00:24:37,642
It's really cool outside.

715
00:24:37,810 --> 00:24:38,710
The room was too hot.

716
00:24:38,878 --> 00:24:39,945
I just realized.

717
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:41,880
Yu Jun.

718
00:24:42,681 --> 00:24:44,181
Come here. Let's take a nap together.

719
00:24:45,651 --> 00:24:47,285
Let me give you an arm pillow.

720
00:24:47,286 --> 00:24:48,453
(Running toward him)

721
00:24:48,454 --> 00:24:50,288
(A baby appears, but not Yu Jun.)

722
00:24:50,289 --> 00:24:51,456
(Sad)

723
00:24:52,625 --> 00:24:54,092
What do you think you are?

724
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,060
You're being so biased between us.

725
00:24:57,062 --> 00:24:58,863
(The living room becomes quiet.)

726
00:25:00,132 --> 00:25:04,202
(Yu Jun watches his uncles lying
on the floor.)

727
00:25:05,137 --> 00:25:06,037
He's tired now.

728
00:25:06,038 --> 00:25:07,138
(Is he finally getting sleepy?)

729
00:25:07,139 --> 00:25:08,339
I think he's going to fall asleep.

730
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,507
Are his eyes closing?

731
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:11,576
- Yes, he's about to.
- His eyes are closing.

732
00:25:12,278 --> 00:25:13,378
If we all pretend to sleep,

733
00:25:13,379 --> 00:25:15,380
he might think he should too.

734
00:25:16,448 --> 00:25:19,717
(He gives SOOBIN an adorable look.)

735
00:25:20,786 --> 00:25:23,488
(Yu Jun seems to be about to fall asleep,
but never does.)

736
00:25:23,489 --> 00:25:24,355
Hey...

737
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:27,291
You don't have to fight sleep
rubbing your eyes like that.

738
00:25:27,292 --> 00:25:28,392
Please try to sleep.

739
00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:31,662
- He's fighting it so hard.
- But he's obviously sleepy.

740
00:25:32,197 --> 00:25:34,665
(SOOBIN is pretending to sleep)

741
00:25:35,934 --> 00:25:37,001
Are you closing your eyes?

742
00:25:37,002 --> 00:25:38,598
(But it doesn't work for Yu Jun.)

743
00:25:39,471 --> 00:25:41,205
He's waking you up
because he knows you're faking.

744
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:42,306
(Right.)
He said I was right.

745
00:25:43,842 --> 00:25:45,843
(He leans back on his arms.)

746
00:25:46,345 --> 00:25:48,980
(Dangling)

747
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:53,017
(He's watching the uncles sleeping.)

748
00:25:54,554 --> 00:25:55,563
Everyone is sleeping.

749
00:25:56,288 --> 00:25:57,221
Everyone fell asleep, Yu Jun.

750
00:25:57,222 --> 00:26:02,693
(Except for Yu Jun and SOOBIN,
everyone is asleep, dreaming.)

751
00:26:04,029 --> 00:26:05,263
(SOOBIN carries Yu Jun back
into the bedroom.)

752
00:26:05,264 --> 00:26:06,230
It got cooler in here.

753
00:26:12,371 --> 00:26:18,042
(He tries again to put Yu Jun to sleep
as he leans on his shoulder.)

754
00:26:18,544 --> 00:26:22,213
(But Yu Jun still doesn't fall asleep
even after over an hour.)

755
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:24,882
(He suddenly sits up
as if someone called him.)

756
00:26:25,617 --> 00:26:27,484
(Looking around)

757
00:26:29,221 --> 00:26:30,988
(Turning)

758
00:26:30,989 --> 00:26:32,390
(Shaking his head...)

759
00:26:32,391 --> 00:26:33,558
(side to side)

760
00:26:33,559 --> 00:26:36,561
(Yu Jun starts playing again.)

761
00:26:39,298 --> 00:26:40,798
(Laughing)

762
00:26:41,467 --> 00:26:45,103
(Perfectly in sync)

763
00:26:45,604 --> 00:26:47,538
(Laughing)

764
00:26:48,373 --> 00:26:53,777
(I'm happy if you're happy.)

765
00:26:54,847 --> 00:26:57,515
(The first day of parenting:)

766
00:26:57,516 --> 00:27:00,251
(It's so exhausting
you feel like you might pass out.)

767
00:27:01,086 --> 00:27:02,891
(What will happen next?)
